[this review was collected as part of a promotion.] natasha denona eye sculpt texture and tone palette in dramatic is my new favorite item in my makeup case!

there are 18 shades including neutral tones to velvety black in smoothe matte, as well as 6 glittering shades ready to party for the holidays!
this palette has everything i need in eyeshadow to take me from daytime to playtime! i love how the neutral tones are on the left side of the case and the dramatic deep tones are on the right. 
the kit also includes a two-sided instruction card which demonstrates how to apply the eyeshadows..
the eyeshadow is rich, and goes on so smoothly with little to no fall-out. (i only noticed a tiny bit with the darkest shades). 
i love how well the colors hold up without fading, and how silky they feel on my eyelids.
it's super easy to wash off, which is great for bold shades.
i really appreciate the creativity that this palette from natasha denona inspires. i've always appreciated the versatility of neutral shades, but love the attention that rich dramatic  eyeshadow provides. a make-up artist friend taught me the importance and versatility of using a good black eyeshadow, not only for dramatic looks, but also to use to thicken eyelashes after applying mascara, and even to use as an eyeliner!
this natasha denona eye sculpt texture and tone palette in dramatic is the best of endless possibilities!

[this review was collected as part of a promotion.] i received the natasha denona dramatic eyeshadow palette a few weeks ago and wanted to really take the time to use it before reviewing.  i have tried her eyeshadows before, but never a big palette like this one.  i prefer a cooler toned shadow palette for my coloring, but these warm shades are absolutely gorgeous.  the formulas of the shadows are like no other brand out there, so creamy and bendable!

[this review was collected as part of a promotion.] what a beautiful falltime pallete! this is the type of gorgeous makeup product that makes me want to learn how to do my makeup better! the amount of pigment payoff is incredible and a little goes a long way, at the same time there are a lot of approachable colors if you're just going for a light/casual look. the shimmers are a great option for just swiping a single color on your lid with some eyeliner and calling it a day. if you're looking to to splurge this is the type of palette that can be used to make limitless different looks (not to mention the payoff is so good that this will last you forever!!)

[this review was collected as part of a promotion.] this pallet easily blends and is very buildable! i was able to create night and day looks as easy as 1,2,3. the provided cue card was a great starting point. the pallet looks and feels high quality and the magnetic closing really seals the deal for me. obsessed.

overall, this lotion offers a luxurious experience that combines effective skincare with a sensory treat.
